# Omninuera
**Role:** AI Intern

Date: [Start Date]

Candidate: **[Candidate Full Name]**

Dear [Candidate Full Name],

We are pleased to offer you a temporary internship position with Omninuera in the role of AI Intern. This letter sets out the key terms of the internship and is editable as required.

## Internship Status
You will be engaged by Omninuera as an intern/trainee for a fixed-term training program and not as a regular employee. This internship is a temporary learning placement for the period set out in this letter and is intended primarily for your training and educational benefit. You will perform tasks under the supervision of your Reporting Manager and the primary purpose of the placement is learning and skills development. You will not be eligible for employee benefits, statutory social security contributions, or employment protections available to regular employees except as expressly provided in writing in this letter or as required by law. Nothing in this letter creates a contract of employment, guarantees ongoing engagement beyond the Internship End Date, or alters the at-will nature of the arrangement.

## Position Details
- Duration: 3 months.
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month (labelled "stipend" and described below as a training allowance).
- Location: Fully remote; candidate based in Bengaluru.
- Engagement type: Internship / temporary engagement. This is not an employment contract and does not, by default, entitle the candidate to employee benefits unless explicitly stated in writing by Omninuera.
- Expected weekly commitment: 20–40 hours per week (flexible scheduling to support remote work). Tasks will be assigned with a training/supervision focus.
- Reporting Manager: [Reporting Manager]

## Key Responsibilities
The AI Intern will be expected to undertake the following responsibilities:
- Data preparation and cleaning for machine learning experiments.
- Setting up and running model experiments and training pipelines.
- Evaluating model performance and producing quantitative and qualitative analyses.
- Documenting experiments, methodologies, and results in a clear, reproducible manner.
- Collaborating with the team to integrate feedback, participate in meetings, and contribute to project planning.

## Stipend, Taxes and Payment
Stipend and Taxes. You will be paid a monthly stipend (training allowance) of INR 10,000 payable in arrears on Omninuera's usual payroll date each month, subject to applicable deductions required by law. The stipend is a training allowance provided in consideration of your participation in the internship program and is not a salary for purposes of employee benefits. You acknowledge and agree that you are responsible for any personal income tax or other tax obligations arising from the stipend; Omninuera may withhold taxes where required by applicable law.

Stipend Payment Schedule. The stipend of INR 10,000 per month will be paid monthly by bank transfer. Please provide bank details for stipend payment: [Bank Account Details for Stipend]. Payments will be processed following receipt of any required documentation and in accordance with Omninuera payroll procedures.

## Confidentiality
1. Definition. "Confidential Information" means non-public information disclosed by Omninuera (or its clients/partners) relating to business, operations, products, services, customers, pricing, strategy, software, algorithms, models, data, trade secrets, technical or business information and any other information reasonably understood to be confidential.

2. Obligations. You shall: (a) hold Confidential Information in strict confidence; (b) not use or disclose it except as necessary to perform your internship duties; and (c) take reasonable measures to protect it with at least the same degree of care that you use for your own confidential information.

3. Exceptions. Confidential Information does not include information that: (a) is or becomes publicly available through no breach by you; (b) was in your lawful possession prior to disclosure and not subject to confidentiality obligations (subject to disclosure of such prior information at the start of the internship); (c) is lawfully received from a third party without breach; or (d) is independently developed by you without using Omninuera's Confidential Information.

4. Return/Destruction. Upon termination or at Omninuera's request, you shall promptly return or permanently destroy (and certify destruction of) all Confidential Information and copies thereof, including material stored on personal devices, subject to any legal retention requirements.

5. Survival. The confidentiality obligations in this clause shall survive termination of this letter for a period of two (2) years for ordinary Confidential Information and indefinitely for trade secrets (to the extent such information qualifies as a trade secret under applicable law).

## Intellectual Property and Works Made During Internship
1. Definitions. "Internship Works" means all inventions, discoveries, designs, works of authorship, software, databases, improvements, processes, developments, designs, documentation, know-how, discoveries, trade secrets and other intellectual property (whether or not patentable or registerable) that you solely or jointly create, conceive, reduce to practice or develop during the term of your internship and in the course of performing duties for Omninuera.

2. Assignment. In consideration of the opportunity to participate in the internship program, the stipend and other consideration provided under this letter, you hereby irrevocably assign and transfer to Omninuera and its successors and assigns all right, title and interest in and to the Internship Works, including all worldwide intellectual property rights and moral rights, to the maximum extent permitted by applicable law. You shall, at Omninuera's request and expense, promptly execute all documents and do all acts that Omninuera reasonably requires to perfect, register, maintain or enforce ownership of such rights.

3. Prior Works. You represent that you have disclosed in writing to Omninuera, prior to commencement of the internship, any inventions, creations or materials you own or have rights to that you intend to use or incorporate in the Internship Works (the "Prior Works"). To the extent any Prior Works are used, those Prior Works shall remain your property and are exempt from this assignment, unless a separate written agreement is executed.

4. Student Projects / Academic Collaborations. If any Internship Works arise from or are subject to academic institution rules or grant obligations, you will notify Omninuera before commencing work so the parties can agree in writing on ownership and license rights.

## Termination and Early Exit
1. Either party may terminate this internship for any reason by providing one (1) week's prior written notice to the other party.

2. Omninuera may terminate your internship without prior notice or payment in lieu where there is cause, including but not limited to gross misconduct, material breach of this letter, serious dishonesty, breach of confidentiality, violation of company policies, or conduct that may damage Omninuera's reputation.

3. Upon termination, Omninuera will pay any unpaid stipend pro-rated to the last working day and will provide reasonable assistance to effect a proper handover of work and return of company property.

## Background Verification and Data Protection
1. Background Checks. Your offer is conditional upon satisfactory completion of identity, educational, employment and criminal background verification checks as may be required by Omninuera. By accepting this offer, you expressly consent to such checks and to Omninuera contacting former employers, educational institutions and other third parties for verification.

2. Personal Data Processing. You consent to Omninuera collecting, storing and processing your personal data for recruitment, onboarding, background checks and related administrative purposes in accordance with applicable law. Omninuera will process such data only for specified purposes, store it securely, and retain it only for as long as necessary (typically no longer than one (1) year after completion/termination of the internship, unless retention is required or permitted under law or necessary for legitimate business purposes).

3. Rights and Contact. If you have questions or want to request correction/deletion of your personal data, contact [data_protection@omninuera.example] (or the appropriate contact). Omninuera will comply with applicable legal obligations in relation to requests and disclosures.

## No Employee Benefits
Except as expressly provided in this letter, you will not be entitled to employee benefits (including but not limited to medical insurance, gratuity, provident fund, paid leave or other retirement benefits) or statutory benefits applicable to employees, and this letter does not create an employment contract.

## Company Policies and Conduct
You will be required to comply with Omninuera policies (including code of conduct, data security and acceptable use policies) while participating in the internship. Omninuera may provide onboarding materials and policies that you must review and acknowledge.

## Governing Law and Jurisdiction
This letter and any dispute arising from it shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. The courts located in Bengaluru, Karnataka shall have exclusive jurisdiction to adjudicate any dispute arising out of or relating to this offer.

## Acceptance
To accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy to the hiring team.

